raw_data.title: .NET Developer II
raw_data.description: Under limited direction, perform design, testing, coding, and developing .NET software to meet user’s needs. Provides tier 2/3 troubleshooting and software maintenance to ensure software applications continue to function normally. Conduct upgrade, and testing; and documentation of the application, service or environment as a reference for future operations and maintenance, including version and platform upgrades. Code software applications to adhere to designs supporting internal business requirements or external customers. Has knowledge of standard concepts, practices, and procedures within a particular field.  Works under general supervision of a Development Team Lead.

raw_data.title: .NET Developer III
raw_data.description: Responsible for designing, testing, coding, and developing .NET software to meet user’s needs; recommending software upgrades for current and future systems; ensuring software continues to function normally through software maintenance, upgrade, and testing; and documenting every aspects of the application, service or environment as a reference for future operations and maintenance, including version and platform upgrades.  Code software applications to adhere to designs supporting internal business requirements or external customers. Standardizes the quality assurance procedure for software development using industry best practices.  Oversees development of fixes and enhancements. Has in-depth knowledge of standard concepts, best practices, and procedures within a particular field. Relies on experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals. May lead and direct the work of others. Typically reports to a project leader or manager.

raw_data.title: Business Analyst I
raw_data.description: Under general supervision, formulates and defines system scope and objectives through research and fact-finding to develop or modify moderately complex information systems. Prepares detailed specifications from which programs will be written.  Reviews, analyzes, and evaluates business systems and user needs and documents requirements as required.

raw_data.title: Customer Support Analyst I
raw_data.description: Provides technical support requiring an entry level technical knowledge of IT products and services. Has a general knowledge of several areas of specialty (hardware, software, desktop, etc.). Acts as a technical resource for more technical problem resolution of a Tier 1 nature. Troubleshoots, analyzes and investigates general technical incidents and communicates solutions via telephone, fax, e-mail, or in person concerning the use of IT products and services to users. Performs analysis and research of the problem and determines solutions to meet client needs. Troubleshoots and analyzes technical problems for end-users regarding a variety of IT products, i.e. hardware, software, and related services.

raw_data.title: Functional Tester II
raw_data.description: Under limited direction, performs evaluation, recommendation and implementation of testing procedures and strategies for products, systems, components, or modifications.  Independently performs the identification of functional testing and leads the analysis, and interpretation of test results. Generate the documentation, definition and maintenance of internal quality control standards and reliability programs. Familiar with standard concepts, practices, and procedures within a particular field. Relies on experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals.  Executes test scripts and determine if system requirements have been met per documented specifications. Performs a variety of complex tasks. A wide degree of creativity and latitude is required. Write test plans and test documentation; review documentation produced by other test team members; provide feedback.. Typically reports to a Test Team Lead.

raw_data.title: Functional Tester III
raw_data.description: Independently performs evaluation, recommendation and implementation of testing procedures and strategies for products, systems, components, or modifications.  Oversees the identification of functional problems and leads the analysis, and interpretation of test results produced by team members. Oversees the documentation, definition and maintenance of internal quality control standards and reliability programs. Familiar with standard concepts, best practices, and procedures within a particular field. Relies on experience and expert judgment to plan and accomplish goals for an integrated test team. Performs a variety of complex tasks. Provide mentorship to junior team members.  Support testing metrics collection and reporting and evaluate testing solutions and make recommendations.  Typically reports to a manager.

raw_data.title: Information Security Specialist II
raw_data.description: Responsible for designing and implementing solutions for protecting the confidentiality, integrity and availability of sensitive information.  Provides technical evaluations of customer systems and assists with making security improvements.  Conducts security product evaluations, and recommends products, technologies and upgrades to improve the customers security posture.  Conducts testing and audit log reviews to evaluate the effectiveness of current security measures. Provides technical support in the areas of vulnerability assessment, risk assessment, network security, product evaluation, and security implementation.

raw_data.title: Infrastructure Engineer I
raw_data.description: Under general direction, responsible for administration and day-to-day operation of organization's local area network (LAN) and server infrastructure. Provides integrated team support and maintenance of data center hardware and software. Maintains integrity of the LAN hardware and software. Installs LAN software upgrades, including planning and scheduling, testing and coordination. Performs LAN security procedures, including implementing login requests. With assistance, evaluates new products and technologies to determine impact on existing system configurations. Provides liaison support between the PC/LAN team, vendors and internal support group as needed. Provides general troubleshooting and resolution of Tier 2 issues related to LAN hardware and software.  Install, configure and maintain operating system and other Commercial of the Shelf (COTS) software products. Perform everyday system administration tasks like create user ids, backup and restore. Move/Add/Change user workstations, which includes IP and Switch administration.

raw_data.title: IT Engineer I
raw_data.description: Responsible for assisting in one or more of the following areas. Designs and develops software applications and hardware in a technical/operational environment; researching and applying computer science methods and techniques to store, manipulate, transform or present information by means of computer systems; and developing methods and techniques to solve complex computer processing requirements. Involved in projects consisting of software design, with limited hardware design, algorithm development and design, software engineering, database theory, computational complexity theory, and computer visualization applied to research and practical applications

raw_data.title: IT Engineer II
raw_data.description: Performs in one or more of the following areas. Designs and develops scientific software applications and hardware in a technical/operational environment; researching and applying computer science methods and techniques to store, manipulate, transform or present information by means of computer systems; and developing methods and techniques to solve complex computer processing requirements. Involved in projects consisting of software design, with limited hardware design, algorithm development and design, software engineering, database theory, computational complexity theory, and computer visualization applied to research and practical applications

raw_data.title: IT Engineer III
raw_data.description: Responsible for providing knowledge in one or more of the following areas. Designs and develops software applications and hardware in a technical/operational environment; researching and applying computer science methods and techniques to store, manipulate, transform or present information by means of computer systems; and developing methods and techniques to solve complex computer processing requirements. Involved in projects consisting of software design, with limited hardware design, algorithm development and design, software engineering, database theory, computational complexity theory, and computer visualization applied to research and practical applications.

raw_data.title: IT Engineer IV
raw_data.description: Advanced experience in one or more of the following areas. Designs and develops software applications and hardware in a technical/operational environment; researching and applying computer science methods and techniques to store, manipulate, transform or present information by means of computer systems; and developing methods and techniques to solve complex computer processing requirements. Involved in projects consisting of software design, with limited hardware design, algorithm development and design, software engineering, database theory, computational complexity theory, and computer visualization applied to research and practical applications

raw_data.title: Program Consultant
raw_data.description: Responsible for assisting with one or more of the following activities. Researches and analyzes basic and complex issues surrounding the processes and systems of an organization or program. Makes recommendations surrounding improving processes, efficiency and practices. Provide program scheduling and tasks management, program risk management, coordinate meetings and technical exchanges, and develop technical documentation for assigned program. Recommends and facilitates quality improvement efforts. May lead re-engineering team and act as project manager in some cases.

raw_data.title: Project Manager II
raw_data.description: Responsible for one or more of the following activities. Manages single or multiple tasks, contracts, or IT projects involving a team of personnel for each. Responsible for the day-to-day contract management, including interfacing and coordinating with customer and employee personnel on progress schedules, ensuring quality, and budgets. Communicates project status, monitors project risks and issues. Gives guidance to employee personnel, and assist with providing employee feedback based on project objectives and requirements. Assists in research and development, and presentation activities that may advance the user’s information knowledge base, analyze management, business, and technical issues related to program management and information systems, provide guidance on management processes and procedures, collaborate on feasibility studies and systems planning, as well as have quality assurance and risk management responsibilities.

raw_data.title: IT SME II
raw_data.description: Considered experts in a technical or functional domain (e.g., enterprise software engineering , hybrid data center infrastructure, cloud engineering, networks, cyber security, data science/engineering, AI/ML, governance, engineering processes/procedures, etc.).  Conducts technical systems analysis, design, architecture, integration, documentation, and implementation of applications, infrastructure, networks, data, or systems.  Responsible for providing in-depth technical knowledge, analysis, advice and solutions on complex problems that need extensive knowledge of the subject matter for effective implementation. Participates as needed in all phases of development and implementation to include planning, analysis, development, testing, integration, documentation, and presentation phases.  Possess specialize knowledge and in-depth experience in particular software, hardware, data science models and AI/ML algorithms, data engineering and warehousing principles, multi-layer network design, cybersecurity countermeasures, or mission systems utilized in an end user environment. Keeps abreast of technological developments and trends (e.g. AI/ML, big data, distributed cloud, metaverse, cybersecurity mesh, etc.) and applies knowledge to implement technical solutions to solve business requirements. SMEs prepare and deliver presentations to colleagues, subordinates, and government representatives.  Supports security and accreditation processes to ensure successful implementation.

raw_data.title: Infrastructure Engineer II
raw_data.description: Under general direction, supports, installs, maintains, troubleshoots, and coordinates the usage of local and wide area networks (LAN and WAN), electronic mail, telecommunications, and PC based systems and related software within a cybersecurity environment; evaluates hardware and software, including peripheral, output, and telecommunications equipment; sets up and administers security procedures; implements policies and procedures and ensures adherence to security procedures.  Design, install, maintain network and infrastructure/communications systems.  Troubleshoot and resolve infrastructure or network issues involving various protocols, topologies, networking hardware, etc. Utilize knowledge of internetworking, computer systems, routers, switches, firewalls, and peripherals to enhance understanding of current network designs and to collaborate with other team members to develop new network designs. Apply technical and business experience and understanding to improve processes and procedures for deploying and maintaining IT infrastructure (hardware and network).  Provides integrated team support and maintenance of data center hardware and software.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer II
raw_data.description: Support the the design, development, testing, and operations of applications. This includes the programmatic integration of third-party components, the introduction of new custom capabilities, modification of existing code, process improvement recommendation, and automation of operations and maintenance tasks. Develop and implement technical efforts to design, build, and deploy technology solutions at the direction of architects, including large-scale data processing, enterprise software applications, computationally intensive statistical modeling, and advanced analytics. Participate in all aspects of the software development life cycle for all solutions, including planning, requirements, development, testing, and quality assurance.  Independently write code to perform data ETL, data aggregation and visualization, and develop and implement cloud-applications using platform as a service (PaaS), infrastructure as a service (IaaS), software as a service (SaaS), and data as a service (DaaS).

raw_data.title: Web Developer II
raw_data.description: Responsible for designing, testing, and developing well designed web-based software coding that is testable, and efficient by using best software development practices to meet user’s needs.  Works with the development team to build mock-ups of intuitive interfaces and develop consistent look and feel for web applications. Updates and maintains style guides and ensure application is 508 compliant designs. Develops, maintains, and ensures compliance of application release management, outage management, and change control processes and standards.  Develops proof-of-concepts and prototypes of easy-to-navigate user interfaces (UIs) that consists of web pages with graphics, icons, and color schemes that are visually appealing and wire frames.  Has familiarity to, or may actually: code, test, debug documents, and implement web applications using a variety of platforms both on premise and on the cloud. Performs UI/UX design on web applications as needed to meet usability requirements.
